<div id="review_1630367459" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1630367459" />
    <a title="Jaymie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6089695-jaymie"><img alt="Jaymie" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1639755832p2/6089695.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1630367459?book_show_action=true">Dec 15, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jaymie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jaymie" href="/user/show/6089695-jaymie">Jaymie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1630367459" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18330712676138286949">3.5-4.0 stars. A very sweet story about sisterhood with a touch of romance, spirits of loved ones gone and forgiveness. I enjoyed the story and the characters. It was predictable at times but a nice easy listen. The narrator was good. Overall the story was almost too sweet. EVERYONE was kind and loving and full of charity and of course that is heart warming but hard to believe it was that realistic. That being said. I was most intrigued with the man who started the home. I looked him up and the </span>
  <span id="freeText18330712676138286949" style="display:none">3.5-4.0 stars. A very sweet story about sisterhood with a touch of romance, spirits of loved ones gone and forgiveness. I enjoyed the story and the characters. It was predictable at times but a nice easy listen. The narrator was good. Overall the story was almost too sweet. EVERYONE was kind and loving and full of charity and of course that is heart warming but hard to believe it was that realistic. That being said. I was most intrigued with the man who started the home. I looked him up and the character Albert Shaw was based on John Groom. What an incredible thing he started. I didn’t read much but I hope he was truly like the character portrayed. He is the type of person that makes hope shine bright for man kind. What a good and pure heart he had. His wife (in the book) also. <br />I liked these quotes from Tilly remembering wisdom shared by her dad. <br /><br />“Fate is what happens to you but destiny is what you desire!”<br /><br />“Sometimes it is better to look at the shadows rather than be dazzled by the sun!”<br /><br /></span>
