    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2268549835" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2268549835" />
    <a title="Gina" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/28627991-gina"><img alt="Gina" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1641736879p2/28627991.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2268549835?book_show_action=true">Mar 02, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Gina" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Gina" href="/user/show/28627991-gina">Gina</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/28627991-gina?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/28627991-gina?shelf=england">england</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/28627991-gina?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/28627991-gina?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2268549835" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14463295435793208592">This book is one of my all time favorites.<br/><br/>The story revolves around Tilly Harper and begins in 1912 London. Tilly, 20, secures a position of Assistant Housemaster at Mr. Shaw&apos;s Home for Watercress and Flower Girls. The home is a place where formerly orphaned or crippled street children are living. There, they create beautiful flowers which are then sold on the streets of Victorian London. <br/><br/>While there, Tilly discovers a diary that was left behind by a flower girl in the late 1800&apos;s. At this point</span>
  <span id="freeText14463295435793208592" style="display:none">This book is one of my all time favorites.<br /><br />The story revolves around Tilly Harper and begins in 1912 London. Tilly, 20, secures a position of Assistant Housemaster at Mr. Shaw's Home for Watercress and Flower Girls. The home is a place where formerly orphaned or crippled street children are living. There, they create beautiful flowers which are then sold on the streets of Victorian London. <br /><br />While there, Tilly discovers a diary that was left behind by a flower girl in the late 1800's. At this point, the book tells the very sad story that is revealed in the diary . The diary belonged to Florrie, who is separated from her beloved sister Rosie. Eventually, Florrie passes away from a broken heart.<br /><br />Tilly decides to find out what happened to Rosie, taking up Florrie's wish to be united with her sister.<br /><br />The book was an extremely emotional read. Your heart will break for the children, unloved and living on the streets, who are taken in to the Home to create posies of violets and watercress to be sold to the lucky wealthy people. You will want Tilly to find Rosie so badly that it will embed itself in your heart.<br /><br />This is one beautiful book.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14463295435793208592" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


